<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 20 at 3:09PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT
CENTRAL SURRY COUNTY THROUGH 345 PM EDT...
At 308 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mountain Park, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fairview...
Dobson...
Mountain Park...
Level Cross...
Rockford...
Ararat...
and Crutchfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
